{"_id":"0N4iB1H7JGGr2rmf","name":"LOTUS PROJECTOR","permission":{"default":0,"kDiJJdMOROJNqvmU":3},"type":"mech_system","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[],"deployables":[{"id":"SVUaRwPLsIiTO1IC","fallback_lid":"dep_ms_lotus_projector_lotus_projector","type":"deployable","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"}],"destroyed":false,"effect":"","lid":"ms_lotus_projector","integrated":[],"license":"SWALLOWTAIL","license_level":1,"name":"LOTUS PROJECTOR","source":{"id":"uxjxh4Hl1iIg58Wcx3S_m","fallback_lid":"SSC","type":"manufacturer","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"},"tags":[{"tag":{"id":"ew40qkTW1h4_fGF9RkHYq","fallback_lid":"tg_invisible","type":"tag","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"}}],"sp":2,"uses":0,"actions":[],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[],"description":"Mech-mounted Lotus Projectors are designed to launch small, actively camouflaged scout drones. The projector fires the single-use drones at subsonic speeds in bursts of ten, blanketing a wide area in order to relay information about terrain and targets within.","type":"System"},"folder":null,"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"1ALBgUAmAxHmAv5m","name":"LUCIFER-CLASS NHP","permission":{"default":0,"kDiJJdMOROJNqvmU":3},"type":"mech_system","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[],"deployables":[],"destroyed":false,"effect":"","lid":"ms_lucifer_class_nhp","integrated":[],"license":"TOKUGAWA","license_level":3,"name":"LUCIFER-CLASS NHP","source":{"id":"3wB3mYKitmiMMsMexoSWW","fallback_lid":"HA","type":"manufacturer","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"},"tags":[{"tag":{"id":"XYqSnHwQZUAis-m-Mqe21","fallback_lid":"tg_ai","type":"tag","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"}},{"tag":{"id":"3s9x9kN8UpSVrXnvEk9Uq","fallback_lid":"tg_unique","type":"tag","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"}},{"val":2,"tag":{"id":"6i_N-6rNndy5Q8xPU9Fnf","fallback_lid":"tg_limited","type":"tag","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"}},{"val":"1d3+3","tag":{"id":"6jesf0ZAVDoYVvILu9-je","fallback_lid":"tg_heat_self","type":"tag","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"}}],"sp":3,"uses":0,"actions":[{"lid":"act_lucifer_protocol","name":"LUCIFER Protocol","activation":"Protocol","terse":"Terse Description","detail":"Expend a charge to give your next ranged or melee attack this turn bonus damage on hit equal to your current heat after activating this protocol, as long as the weapon deals any energy.","cost":1,"frequency":"","init":"","trigger":"","pilot":false,"mech":true,"heat_cost":0,"synergy_locations":[],"damage":[],"range":[],"confirm":["CONFIRM LUCIFER Protocol"],"hide_active":false,"ignore_used":false,"log":""}],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[],"description":"LUCIFER came to the Think Tank’s attention after their repeated victories in thought-war games. LUCIFER clones are characterized by their brash, enthusiastic personality, often expressing frustration with timid pilots. This bombastic personality hides a calculating, brilliant tactical mind that feeds constant information to pilots – often faster than they can process it.<br>LUCIFER’s combat doctrine demands action, appearing to less daring pilots as a chaotic blend of reckless maneuvering and aggressive offense that keeps defenders beleaguered and unable to respond. Pilots looking to partner with LUCIFER clones should be aware that this attack style is likely to leave them vulnerable to counterattack, and also that these NHPs enjoy what they call “good-natured ribbing”.","type":"System"},"folder":null,"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"2jKyKxgcX3nwIl4i","name":"EXTERNAL AMMO FEED","permission":{"default":0,"kDiJJdMOROJNqvmU":3},"type":"mech_system","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[],"deployables":[],"destroyed":false,"effect":"","lid":"ms_external_ammo_feed","integrated":[],"license":"BARBAROSSA","license_level":3,"name":"EXTERNAL AMMO FEED","source":{"id":"3wB3mYKitmiMMsMexoSWW","fallback_lid":"HA","type":"manufacturer","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"},"tags":[{"tag":{"id":"3s9x9kN8UpSVrXnvEk9Uq","fallback_lid":"tg_unique","type":"tag","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"}},{"val":"1d3+1","tag":{"id":"6jesf0ZAVDoYVvILu9-je","fallback_lid":"tg_heat_self","type":"tag","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"}}],"sp":3,"uses":0,"actions":[{"lid":"act_aUyyFciOB33YZ1QKdLt9b","name":"New Action","activation":"Quick","terse":"Terse Description","detail":"1/round, you can activate this system to reload a Loading weapon.","cost":1,"frequency":"","init":"","trigger":"","pilot":false,"mech":true,"heat_cost":0,"synergy_locations":[],"damage":[],"range":[],"confirm":["CONFIRM undefined"],"hide_active":false,"ignore_used":false,"log":""}],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[],"description":"An external ammo feed is any sort of ammunition beyond what is carried in a mech’s integrated storage: from magazines strapped to bodies or limbs; battery packs attached to hip clasps; or massive, dorsal-mounted ammunition and charge packs, externals ensure that pilots have more than enough boom to get the job done.","type":"System"},"folder":null,"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"2uPyGIRgu38QrgNA","name":"TRACKING BUG","permission":{"default":0,"kDiJJdMOROJNqvmU":3},"type":"mech_system","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[],"deployables":[],"destroyed":false,"effect":"","lid":"ms_tracking_bug","integrated":[],"license":"DEATH’S HEAD","license_level":1,"name":"TRACKING BUG","source":{"id":"uxjxh4Hl1iIg58Wcx3S_m","fallback_lid":"SSC","type":"manufacturer","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"},"tags":[],"sp":2,"uses":0,"actions":[{"lid":"act_ZcvxQAQo08BWQoNDK4w1_","name":"New Action","activation":"Quick Tech","terse":"Terse Description","detail":"Make a tech attack against a character within Sensors. On a hit, you know their exact location, HP, Structure, and Speed for the duration. They can’t Hide and you ignore their Invisible status. To remove the tracking drone, they must succeed on an Engineering check as a quick action; otherwise it deactivates at the end of the scene.","cost":1,"frequency":"","init":"","trigger":"","pilot":false,"mech":true,"heat_cost":0,"synergy_locations":[],"damage":[],"range":[],"confirm":["CONFIRM undefined"],"hide_active":false,"ignore_used":false,"log":""}],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[],"description":"Tracking bugs are specialized tracer rounds – essentially, drones too large to be classified as nanites, and far too small to fit the Union-standard parameters of a drone. Fired from dedicated launchers, tracking bugs guide themselves toward their designated target. Following successful penetration of the target, they surreptitiously and continuously feed live data back to their registered user.","type":"System"},"folder":null,"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"3EGvxftWAlVo401C","name":"FLICKER FIELD PROJECTOR","permission":{"default":0,"kDiJJdMOROJNqvmU":3},"type":"mech_system","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[],"deployables":[],"destroyed":false,"effect":"Whenever you Boost or make a standard move, you project a holographic pattern around you, leaving dazzling afterimages that make it hard to discern your precise location: you count as Invisible the next time you’re attacked. You can only benefit from one instance of this effect at a time.","lid":"ms_flicker_field_projector","integrated":[],"license":"DUSK WING","license_level":2,"name":"FLICKER FIELD PROJECTOR","source":{"id":"uxjxh4Hl1iIg58Wcx3S_m","fallback_lid":"SSC","type":"manufacturer","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"},"tags":[{"tag":{"id":"3s9x9kN8UpSVrXnvEk9Uq","fallback_lid":"tg_unique","type":"tag","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"}}],"sp":1,"uses":0,"actions":[],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[{"locations":["move","boost"],"detail":"Whenever you Boost or make a standard move, you project a holographic pattern around you, leaving dazzling afterimages that make it hard to discern your precise location: you count as Invisible the next time you’re attacked. You can only benefit from one instance of this effect at a time.","system_types":["any"],"weapon_types":["any"],"weapon_sizes":["any"]}],"description":"“I saw myself over and over and over and over and over and over and over and–”","type":"System"},"folder":null,"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"3kPbki94fTBJL4Jc","name":"//SCORPION V70.1","permission":{"default":0,"kDiJJdMOROJNqvmU":3},"type":"mech_system","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[],"deployables":[],"destroyed":false,"effect":"Any time you or any allied character adjacent to you is missed by a tech attack or succeed on a save against a hostile tech action, choose one of the following:<ul><li>The attacker becomes Impaired until the end of their next turn and takes 2 heat.</li><li>The attacker becomes Jammed until the end of their next turn.</li></ul>","lid":"ms___scorpion_v70.1","integrated":[],"license":"GORGON","license_level":2,"name":"//SCORPION V70.1","source":{"id":"hlTH_kILadfAwbZJVe4hQ","fallback_lid":"HORUS","type":"manufacturer","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"},"tags":[{"tag":{"id":"3s9x9kN8UpSVrXnvEk9Uq","fallback_lid":"tg_unique","type":"tag","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"}}],"sp":2,"uses":0,"actions":[],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[],"description":"The //SCORPION program has a long history on the omninet despite its rather mundane operation (for HORUS-tagged code, at least). Traced back to pre-Deimos theorycode found on an obscure research paper discussing pre-NHP machine mind reflex-responses, //SCORPION evolved from a simple packet interpreter to a robust anti-incursion program, nimble enough to adapt to most any market-line system that receives its broadcast.","type":"System"},"folder":null,"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"3pMX5c7MwetYFxem","name":"ERR: DATA NOT FOUND","permission":{"default":0,"kDiJJdMOROJNqvmU":3},"type":"mech_system","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[],"deployables":[],"destroyed":false,"effect":"COMP/CON is unable to retrieve the data necessary to furnish this System. This is likely the result of a missing or outdated content pack.","lid":"missing_mechsystem","integrated":[],"license":"GMS","license_level":0,"name":"ERR: DATA NOT FOUND","source":{"id":"FA3YWcjrTHuhIt7L-7OKc","fallback_lid":"GMS","type":"manufacturer","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"},"tags":[],"sp":1,"uses":0,"actions":[],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[],"description":"COMP/CON is unable to retrieve the data necessary to furnish this System. This is likely the result of a missing or outdated content pack.","type":"System"},"folder":null,"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"3r514y6DkGkxBsEE","name":"SWARM BODY","permission":{"default":0,"kDiJJdMOROJNqvmU":3},"type":"mech_system","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[],"deployables":[],"destroyed":false,"effect":"","lid":"ms_swarm_body","integrated":[],"license":"BALOR","license_level":2,"name":"SWARM BODY","source":{"id":"hlTH_kILadfAwbZJVe4hQ","fallback_lid":"HORUS","type":"manufacturer","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"},"tags":[{"tag":{"id":"3s9x9kN8UpSVrXnvEk9Uq","fallback_lid":"tg_unique","type":"tag","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"}}],"sp":2,"uses":0,"actions":[{"lid":"act_nwumJm4MNh2B7puSqjXOR","name":"New Action","activation":"Quick","terse":"Terse Description","detail":"After activating this system, a burst 1 swarm is released at the end of your turn. Characters of your choice that start their turn in the area or enter it on their turn must succeed on a Systems save or take 3 kinetic. This amount increases by +3 damage for each of your turns that you have remained stationary, up to a maximum of 9 kinetic.<br>This effect lasts until you move, including involuntary movement.","cost":1,"frequency":"","init":"","trigger":"","pilot":false,"mech":true,"heat_cost":0,"synergy_locations":[],"damage":[],"range":[],"confirm":["CONFIRM undefined"],"hide_active":false,"ignore_used":false,"log":""}],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[],"description":"What must it have been like for him? For the man who called himself Maw? For all of his followers? Certainly they had families before. Memories. Loves. Fears. Private thoughts. All gone. All of their bodies shattered. All of their minds spread across a billion lesser forms. Translated from the singular – all of its imperfections and lesser-lesser-thans – to become as air, and the clouds that fill it, and the wind that shapes the world.","type":"System"},"folder":null,"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"42lSof9pnwbxYVqb","name":"KINETIC COMPENSATOR","permission":{"default":0,"kDiJJdMOROJNqvmU":3},"type":"mech_system","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[],"deployables":[],"destroyed":false,"effect":"When you miss with a ranged attack roll, your next ranged attack roll gains +1 accuracy.","lid":"ms_kinetic_compensator","integrated":[],"license":"DEATH’S HEAD","license_level":3,"name":"KINETIC COMPENSATOR","source":{"id":"uxjxh4Hl1iIg58Wcx3S_m","fallback_lid":"SSC","type":"manufacturer","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"},"tags":[{"tag":{"id":"3s9x9kN8UpSVrXnvEk9Uq","fallback_lid":"tg_unique","type":"tag","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"}}],"sp":2,"uses":0,"actions":[],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[{"locations":["weapon"],"detail":"When you miss with a ranged attack roll, your next ranged attack roll gains +1 accuracy.","system_types":["any"],"weapon_types":["Rifle","Cannon","Launcher","CQB","Nexus"],"weapon_sizes":["any"]}],"description":"Kinetic compensators are popular enhancements, providing a subsurface framework of electronically modulated gyroscopes and hydraulic compensators that work in concert to absorb and disperse recoil caused by firing heavy weapons.","type":"System"},"folder":null,"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"46VWlTpSB6V6buQg","name":"HARDLIGHT DEFENSE SYSTEM","permission":{"default":0,"kDiJJdMOROJNqvmU":3},"type":"mech_system","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[],"deployables":[],"destroyed":false,"effect":"","lid":"ms_hardlight_defense_system","integrated":[],"license":"SALADIN","license_level":2,"name":"HARDLIGHT DEFENSE SYSTEM","source":{"id":"3wB3mYKitmiMMsMexoSWW","fallback_lid":"HA","type":"manufacturer","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"},"tags":[{"tag":{"id":"3s9x9kN8UpSVrXnvEk9Uq","fallback_lid":"tg_unique","type":"tag","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"}},{"tag":{"id":"m4L8W_LqSLTGOqxV78i-U","fallback_lid":"tg_shield","type":"tag","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"}},{"val":2,"tag":{"id":"6jesf0ZAVDoYVvILu9-je","fallback_lid":"tg_heat_self","type":"tag","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"}}],"sp":3,"uses":0,"actions":[{"lid":"act_BVpPk42F7zeqANGVf2lB6","name":"New Action","activation":"Full","terse":"Terse Description","detail":"This system creates a burst 3 hardlight shield. While the shield is in place, you become Immobilized. It blocks line of sight in both directions, and no attacks or effects can pass through (even if they don’t require line of sight). Characters partially within the affected area ignore this effect and draw line of sight as usual.<br>Characters can pass through the shield, but when crossing the perimeter for the first time in a round or starting their turn overlapping the boundary, they take 2 Burn.<br>This shield lasts for the rest of the scene, or until deactivated as a protocol.","cost":1,"frequency":"","init":"","trigger":"","pilot":false,"mech":true,"heat_cost":0,"synergy_locations":[],"damage":[],"range":[],"confirm":["CONFIRM undefined"],"hide_active":false,"ignore_used":false,"log":""},{"lid":"act_deactivate_hardlight_defense_system","name":"Deactivate Hardlight Defense System","activation":"Protocol","terse":"Terse Description","detail":"Deactivate the Hardlight Defense System, removing the Immobilized condition it inflicts.","cost":1,"frequency":"","init":"","trigger":"","pilot":false,"mech":true,"heat_cost":0,"synergy_locations":[],"damage":[],"range":[],"confirm":["CONFIRM Deactivate Hardlight Defense System"],"hide_active":false,"ignore_used":false,"log":""}],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[],"description":"The Hardlight Defense System is an imperfect implementation of theoretically perfect technology. Currently in development by Think Tank NHPs and engineers, hardlight devices project tight, stable waves of light – akin to lasers – that repel matter and energy. In effect, this creates a solid surface, useful for shielding or temporary barrier construction; however, current technology is unable to lower the ambient temperature enough to prevent these surfaces from burning organic matter.","type":"System"},"folder":null,"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"4K5EjAPvBK8MFlH8","name":"ATHENA-CLASS NHP","permission":{"default":0,"kDiJJdMOROJNqvmU":3},"type":"mech_system","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[],"deployables":[],"destroyed":false,"effect":"Your mech gains the AI tag and Simulacrum.","lid":"ms_athena_class_nhp","integrated":[],"license":"SWALLOWTAIL","license_level":3,"name":"ATHENA-CLASS NHP","source":{"id":"uxjxh4Hl1iIg58Wcx3S_m","fallback_lid":"SSC","type":"manufacturer","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"},"tags":[{"tag":{"id":"XYqSnHwQZUAis-m-Mqe21","fallback_lid":"tg_ai","type":"tag","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"}},{"tag":{"id":"3s9x9kN8UpSVrXnvEk9Uq","fallback_lid":"tg_unique","type":"tag","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"}}],"sp":3,"uses":0,"actions":[{"lid":"act_simulacrum","name":"Simulacrum","activation":"Quick","terse":"Terse Description","detail":"ATHENA constructs a perfect, real-time, and fully interactive 3D model of a blast 3 area within range 50, including moving characters, all rendered in lovingly extreme detail. The following effects apply:<ul><li>You have full visibility within the affected area, but it doesn’t count as line of sight.</li><li>You know all statistics, weapons, and systems of characters within the affected area.</li><li>Hostile characters within the affected area don’t benefit from cover and can’t Hide or become Invisible.</li><li>Hostile characters that end their turn in the affected area receive Lock On and cease to be Invisible or Hidden.</li></ul>ATHENA’s simulation lasts until the end of the scene, or about 30 minutes within the narrative. You may target a new area as a quick action.","cost":1,"frequency":"","init":"","trigger":"","pilot":false,"mech":true,"heat_cost":0,"synergy_locations":[],"damage":[],"range":[],"confirm":["CONFIRM Simulacrum"],"hide_active":false,"ignore_used":false,"log":""}],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[],"description":"Smith-Shimano’s ATHENA is the pinnacle of total hyperspectral environmental facsimiles. Through a combination of unfettered omninet access, hyperspectral relays fired out from a Cloudscout TACSIM projector, sub-networked squadmates, and active/hostile intrusion protocols, ATHENA bootstraps a near-flawless reconstruction of the immediate environment around its host core. ATHENA is unparalleled in its processing power, and with this reconstructed environment, it provides trustworthy, accurate advice to pilots in need of strategic counsel.<br>ATHENA clones tend to be patient, cautious, and measured in their relations with their pilots.","type":"System"},"folder":null,"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"5tDeMdCeG2qO8H3T","name":"TYPE-3 PROJECTED SHIELD","permission":{"default":0,"kDiJJdMOROJNqvmU":3},"type":"mech_system","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[],"deployables":[],"destroyed":false,"effect":"","lid":"ms_type_3_projected_shield","integrated":[],"license":"GMS","license_level":0,"name":"TYPE-3 PROJECTED SHIELD","source":{"id":"FA3YWcjrTHuhIt7L-7OKc","fallback_lid":"GMS","type":"manufacturer","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"},"tags":[{"tag":{"id":"m4L8W_LqSLTGOqxV78i-U","fallback_lid":"tg_shield","type":"tag","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"}},{"tag":{"id":"3s9x9kN8UpSVrXnvEk9Uq","fallback_lid":"tg_unique","type":"tag","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"}},{"val":1,"tag":{"id":"6jesf0ZAVDoYVvILu9-je","fallback_lid":"tg_heat_self","type":"tag","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"}}],"sp":2,"uses":0,"actions":[{"lid":"act_project_shield","name":"Project Shield","activation":"Protocol","terse":"Terse Description","detail":"Nominate a character within line of sight: all ranged or melee attacks that they make against you or that you make against them gain +2 Difficulty until the start of your next turn.","cost":1,"frequency":"","init":"","trigger":"","pilot":false,"mech":true,"heat_cost":0,"synergy_locations":[],"damage":[],"range":[],"confirm":["CONFIRM Project Shield"],"hide_active":false,"ignore_used":false,"log":""}],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[],"description":"The GMS Type-3 Projected Shield traps and denies incoming projectiles by projecting an aggressive, superpositional anti-ballistic barrier.","type":"System"},"folder":null,"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"5tvFGIZYOzOO2514","name":"AEGIS SHIELD GENERATOR","permission":{"default":0,"kDiJJdMOROJNqvmU":3},"type":"mech_system","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[],"deployables":[{"id":"iY3PaXiW1h3DBJFW","fallback_lid":"dep_ms_aegis_shield_generator_aegis_shield_generator","type":"deployable","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"}],"destroyed":false,"effect":"","lid":"ms_aegis_shield_generator","integrated":[],"license":"DRAKE","license_level":2,"name":"AEGIS SHIELD GENERATOR","source":{"id":"HnhUqNAPy7nMHu7TP05sG","fallback_lid":"IPS-N","type":"manufacturer","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"},"tags":[{"tag":{"id":"3s9x9kN8UpSVrXnvEk9Uq","fallback_lid":"tg_unique","type":"tag","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"}},{"val":1,"tag":{"id":"6i_N-6rNndy5Q8xPU9Fnf","fallback_lid":"tg_limited","type":"tag","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"}}],"sp":2,"uses":0,"actions":[],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[],"description":"The Aegis is a portable electromagnetic shield generator: a powerful and reliable method – if crude by modern standards – for establishing kinetic and coherent-particle deterrence over a wide area.","type":"System"},"folder":null,"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"65o2P0ILVxk3rOIL","name":"H0R_OS SYSTEM UPGRADE I","permission":{"default":0,"kDiJJdMOROJNqvmU":3},"type":"mech_system","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[],"deployables":[],"destroyed":false,"effect":"","lid":"ms_h0r_os_system_upgrade_i","integrated":[],"license":"GOBLIN","license_level":1,"name":"H0R_OS SYSTEM UPGRADE I","source":{"id":"hlTH_kILadfAwbZJVe4hQ","fallback_lid":"HORUS","type":"manufacturer","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"},"tags":[{"tag":{"id":"3s9x9kN8UpSVrXnvEk9Uq","fallback_lid":"tg_unique","type":"tag","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"}}],"sp":2,"uses":0,"actions":[{"lid":"act_puppet_system.","name":"Puppet System.","activation":"Invade","terse":"Terse Description","detail":"Your target moves its maximum Speed in a direction of your choice. They can be moved into hazardous areas and other obstacles, but are still affected by difficult terrain, obstructions, and so on. This movement is involuntary, but provokes reactions and Engagement as normal and doesn’t count as Knockback, pushing, or pulling.","cost":1,"frequency":"","init":"","trigger":"","pilot":false,"mech":true,"heat_cost":0,"synergy_locations":[],"damage":[],"range":[],"confirm":["CONFIRM Puppet System."],"hide_active":false,"ignore_used":false,"log":""},{"lid":"act_eject_power_cores","name":"Eject Power Cores","activation":"Invade","terse":"Terse Description","detail":"Your target becomes Jammed until the end of their next turn as you temporarily disrupt their systems, ejecting ammo magazines and cooling rods. Characters adjacent to your target take 2 energy damage. This can only be used 1/scene on each character.","cost":1,"frequency":"","init":"","trigger":"","pilot":false,"mech":true,"heat_cost":0,"synergy_locations":[],"damage":[],"range":[],"confirm":["CONFIRM Eject Power Cores"],"hide_active":false,"ignore_used":false,"log":""}],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[],"description":"This system upgrade appears to add auxiliary INSTINCT systems that are capable of autonomous operation independent of the base INSTINCT rig, increasing the efficacy of systemic invasion attempts. Pilots report unnerving low-frequency humming when this tech is installed without the parent rig.","type":"System"},"folder":null,"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"6CEjZa3iCO5IuJIj","name":"PERIMETER COMMAND PLATE","permission":{"default":0,"kDiJJdMOROJNqvmU":3},"type":"mech_system","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[],"deployables":[{"id":"PxNe9h6zwYbj479F","fallback_lid":"dep_ms_perimeter_command_plate_perimeter_command_plate","type":"deployable","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"}],"destroyed":false,"effect":"","lid":"ms_perimeter_command_plate","integrated":[],"license":"BLACK WITCH","license_level":2,"name":"PERIMETER COMMAND PLATE","source":{"id":"uxjxh4Hl1iIg58Wcx3S_m","fallback_lid":"SSC","type":"manufacturer","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"},"tags":[{"tag":{"id":"3s9x9kN8UpSVrXnvEk9Uq","fallback_lid":"tg_unique","type":"tag","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"}}],"sp":2,"uses":0,"actions":[],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[],"description":"The Exotic Materials Group developed the Perimeter Command Plate to extend the area of the Black Witch’s zone of control. Utilizing single-pattern flash printers, the Black Witch prints a broad, circular plate seeded with electromagnetic projectors. Although the plates are intended to be disposable, Black Witch pilots often grow attached to their “familiars” and request their flash-printers create personalized plates.","type":"System"},"folder":null,"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"6qbKPCqXZSOmeNg7","name":"ICEOUT DRONE","permission":{"default":0,"kDiJJdMOROJNqvmU":3},"type":"mech_system","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[],"deployables":[{"id":"aAcnuIHkJMXUn1eT","fallback_lid":"dep_ms_iceout_drone_iceout_drone","type":"deployable","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"}],"destroyed":false,"effect":"Expend a charge to deploy an ICEOUT drone to a free space within Sensors and line of sight, where it hovers in place and generates a burst 1 field.","lid":"ms_iceout_drone","integrated":[],"license":"BLACK WITCH","license_level":2,"name":"ICEOUT DRONE","source":{"id":"uxjxh4Hl1iIg58Wcx3S_m","fallback_lid":"SSC","type":"manufacturer","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"},"tags":[{"val":2,"tag":{"id":"6i_N-6rNndy5Q8xPU9Fnf","fallback_lid":"tg_limited","type":"tag","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"}},{"tag":{"id":"3s9x9kN8UpSVrXnvEk9Uq","fallback_lid":"tg_unique","type":"tag","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"}}],"sp":2,"uses":0,"actions":[],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[],"description":"SSC’s ICEOUT drone is a response to increasing reliance on hostile system scans for accurate targeting. By blanketing a mech’s systems in layers of digital defilade, mirroring, spoofing, and redirection, an ICEOUT drone can effectively disappear or disincorporate it from hostile scans. ICEOUT drones only make their operator system-invisible, however; they remain visible with optics.","type":"System"},"folder":null,"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"6uMpr40R0uiqYRKM","name":"METAFOLD CARVER","permission":{"default":0,"kDiJJdMOROJNqvmU":3},"type":"mech_system","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[],"deployables":[],"destroyed":false,"effect":"","lid":"ms_metafold_carver","integrated":[],"license":"MINOTAUR","license_level":2,"name":"METAFOLD CARVER","source":{"id":"hlTH_kILadfAwbZJVe4hQ","fallback_lid":"HORUS","type":"manufacturer","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"},"tags":[],"sp":2,"uses":0,"actions":[{"lid":"act_ophidian_trek","name":"Ophidian Trek","activation":"Invade","terse":"Terse Description","detail":"Your target is teleported 1d6+1 spaces directly toward you, or as close as possible. If this effect would move them to a space occupied by a character, object, or piece of terrain, the teleport fails.","cost":1,"frequency":"","init":"","trigger":"","pilot":false,"mech":true,"heat_cost":0,"synergy_locations":[],"damage":[],"range":[],"confirm":["CONFIRM Ophidian Trek"],"hide_active":false,"ignore_used":false,"log":""},{"lid":"act_fold_space","name":"Fold Space","activation":"Invade","terse":"Terse Description","detail":"Your target disappears from the battlefield until the start of its next turn. It returns in the same space they disappeared from, or in a free space of their choice as close as possible.","cost":1,"frequency":"","init":"","trigger":"","pilot":false,"mech":true,"heat_cost":0,"synergy_locations":[],"damage":[],"range":[],"confirm":["CONFIRM Fold Space"],"hide_active":false,"ignore_used":false,"log":""}],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[],"description":"<span class='horus--subtle'>[another gift i give to you, little one (am I not kind?): what is a puzzle but a question lost in the asking? do you feel joy when you find that last piece? what do you do with a question that has been answered? what joy is there in knowledge?]</span><br><span class='horus--subtle'>[no, no. there is only joy in seeking. there is only joy in the question]</span>","type":"System"},"folder":null,"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"6xc7gwoxLJIchpIp","name":"HUNTER LOCK","permission":{"default":0,"kDiJJdMOROJNqvmU":3},"type":"mech_system","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[],"deployables":[],"destroyed":false,"effect":"","lid":"ms_hunter_lock","integrated":[],"license":"PEGASUS","license_level":1,"name":"HUNTER LOCK","source":{"id":"hlTH_kILadfAwbZJVe4hQ","fallback_lid":"HORUS","type":"manufacturer","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"},"tags":[{"tag":{"id":"3s9x9kN8UpSVrXnvEk9Uq","fallback_lid":"tg_unique","type":"tag","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"}}],"sp":2,"uses":0,"actions":[{"lid":"act_ID4Uy42Coi8KaRkToCARt","name":"New Action","activation":"Quick","terse":"Terse Description","detail":"Choose a character within Sensors: for the rest of the scene, your first successful ranged or melee attack against them each round deals +3 bonus damage. You cannot choose a new target until your current target is destroyed or the scene ends.","cost":1,"frequency":"","init":"","trigger":"","pilot":false,"mech":true,"heat_cost":0,"synergy_locations":[],"damage":[],"range":[],"confirm":["CONFIRM undefined"],"hide_active":false,"ignore_used":false,"log":""}],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[],"description":"“A mind’s first charge is to never lose sight of her enemy. When she can affix them in her eye, she can kill them with a blink.”<ul><li>Excerpt from the Boundary Codex.</li></ul>","type":"System"},"folder":null,"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"7zfj6RhKvMjAurFc","name":"STABLE STRUCTURE","permission":{"default":0,"kDiJJdMOROJNqvmU":3},"type":"mech_system","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[],"deployables":[],"destroyed":false,"effect":"You gain +1 Accuracy on saves to avoid Prone or Knockback.","lid":"ms_stable_structure","integrated":[],"license":"GMS","license_level":0,"name":"STABLE STRUCTURE","source":{"id":"FA3YWcjrTHuhIt7L-7OKc","fallback_lid":"GMS","type":"manufacturer","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"},"tags":[{"tag":{"id":"3s9x9kN8UpSVrXnvEk9Uq","fallback_lid":"tg_unique","type":"tag","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"}}],"sp":2,"uses":0,"actions":[],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[],"description":"No description","type":"System"},"folder":null,"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"8dPbe3HMsKJ6YjkT","name":"LB/OC CLOAKING FIELD","permission":{"default":0,"kDiJJdMOROJNqvmU":3},"type":"mech_system","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[],"deployables":[],"destroyed":false,"effect":"","lid":"ms_lb_oc_cloaking_field","integrated":[],"license":"SWALLOWTAIL","license_level":3,"name":"LB/OC CLOAKING FIELD","source":{"id":"uxjxh4Hl1iIg58Wcx3S_m","fallback_lid":"SSC","type":"manufacturer","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"},"tags":[{"val":2,"tag":{"id":"6jesf0ZAVDoYVvILu9-je","fallback_lid":"tg_heat_self","type":"tag","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"}}],"sp":4,"uses":0,"actions":[{"lid":"act_5XKk1YFpfxtM-fMdQQg9O","name":"New Action","activation":"Quick","terse":"Terse Description","detail":"You become Slowed, but your Mech and all allied characters within a burst 2 area become Invisible as long as they remain completely inside the area. This effect lasts until the end of your next turn, or until you are Stunned, take damage, or deactivate it as a quick action.","cost":1,"frequency":"","init":"","trigger":"","pilot":false,"mech":true,"heat_cost":0,"synergy_locations":[],"damage":[],"range":[],"confirm":["CONFIRM undefined"],"hide_active":false,"ignore_used":false,"log":""}],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[],"description":"SSC’s mil-spec cloaking field is the result of extensive experimentation in cooling and light-reflecting sciences. Born from a need to reflect harmful radiation away from ships and EVA modules in deep space, the Lightbend/Overcloak (LB/OC) cloaking field is often used by rangers and long-patrol scout pilots to ensure not only radiation protection, but optical concealment as well. The light- and radiation-bending properties of the LB/OC conceals anything inside of its projected bubble from sensor suites and optical spotting.","type":"System"},"folder":null,"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"8wLrcabsLsuBUDmu","name":"WEBJAW SNARE","permission":{"default":0,"kDiJJdMOROJNqvmU":3},"type":"mech_system","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[],"deployables":[{"id":"tFSUbW1u0NVUrLa1","fallback_lid":"dep_ms_webjaw_snare_webjaw_snare","type":"deployable","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"}],"destroyed":false,"effect":"Expend a charge to deploy a Webjaw snare to a free, adjacent space, where it arms at the end of your turn.","lid":"ms_webjaw_snare","integrated":[],"license":"VLAD","license_level":1,"name":"WEBJAW SNARE","source":{"id":"HnhUqNAPy7nMHu7TP05sG","fallback_lid":"IPS-N","type":"manufacturer","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"},"tags":[{"val":2,"tag":{"id":"6i_N-6rNndy5Q8xPU9Fnf","fallback_lid":"tg_limited","type":"tag","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"}},{"tag":{"id":"3s9x9kN8UpSVrXnvEk9Uq","fallback_lid":"tg_unique","type":"tag","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"}}],"sp":1,"uses":0,"actions":[],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[],"description":"Suitable for use in any theater, the IPS-N Webjaw Explosively Accelerated Filament system is a deployable perimeter defense solution designed to arrest hostile movement in predetermined kill-corridors. The Webjaw consists of a networked cluster of single-use anchors, each consisting of a barb, a coil of arachnosynth NoCut filament, and an explosive charge.<br>When triggered remotely, or by a series of programmable physical, electronic, or chemical triggers, the anchors fire, embedding barbs deep inside targets, whether soft or hard. The barbs, secured to anchor points by NoCut filament, clog and restrict movement, fouling gears, wheels, rotors, engines, and all methods of locomotion.","type":"System"},"folder":null,"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"8zoTrZjNeauLPR0b","name":"H0R_OS SYSTEM UPGRADE III","permission":{"default":0,"kDiJJdMOROJNqvmU":3},"type":"mech_system","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[],"deployables":[],"destroyed":false,"effect":"","lid":"ms_h0r_os_system_upgrade_iii","integrated":[],"license":"GOBLIN","license_level":3,"name":"H0R_OS SYSTEM UPGRADE III","source":{"id":"hlTH_kILadfAwbZJVe4hQ","fallback_lid":"HORUS","type":"manufacturer","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"},"tags":[{"tag":{"id":"3s9x9kN8UpSVrXnvEk9Uq","fallback_lid":"tg_unique","type":"tag","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"}}],"sp":2,"uses":0,"actions":[{"lid":"act_dimensional_emblems","name":"Dimensional Emblems","activation":"Invade","terse":"Terse Description","detail":"You create three Size 1 data constructs in free spaces adjacent to your target, but not adjacent to each other. When a character passes through one of the constructs, they take 2 heat and the construct disappears. They last for the rest of the scene or until either they are destroyed, you take this action again, or you delete them as a free action. A construct can be destroyed by an adjacent character with a successful Systems skill check as a quick action.","cost":1,"frequency":"","init":"","trigger":"","pilot":false,"mech":true,"heat_cost":0,"synergy_locations":[],"damage":[],"range":[],"confirm":["CONFIRM Dimensional Emblems"],"hide_active":false,"ignore_used":false,"log":""},{"lid":"act_celestial_shackles","name":"Celestial Shackles","activation":"Invade","terse":"Terse Description","detail":"Mark a space your target currently occupies. If they leave the affected space, once at any point during your turn, you may take a free action to teleport them back to that space, or as close as possible, ending this effect. An affected character can attempt to succeed on a Systems save as a quick action to end the effect, otherwise it lasts until the end of the scene.","cost":1,"frequency":"","init":"","trigger":"","pilot":false,"mech":true,"heat_cost":0,"synergy_locations":[],"damage":[],"range":[],"confirm":["CONFIRM Celestial Shackles"],"hide_active":false,"ignore_used":false,"log":""}],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[],"description":"H0r_OS III is installed in the form of unstable, self-iterating code that provides massive tactical benefits when it completes. Pilots often report strange mutations or additions in the codebase that resemble a liturgy and suggest self-awareness.<br>Building on the tech underpinning the H0r_OS II’s manifested Other, H0r_OS III weaponizes the projection, creating a contained entropic zone that is incredibly dangerous to organic life and systemic integrity.","type":"System"},"folder":null,"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"9GXeMh7GlL7p0UfU","name":"Ammo Case II","permission":{"default":0,"kDiJJdMOROJNqvmU":3},"type":"mech_system","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[],"deployables":[],"destroyed":false,"effect":"1/turn, when you attack with a Main ranged weapon, you may expend charges to apply one of the following effects to your attack at the listed cost.","lid":"ms_walking_armory_2","integrated":[],"license":"GMS","license_level":0,"name":"Ammo Case II","source":null,"tags":[{"val":6,"tag":{"id":"6i_N-6rNndy5Q8xPU9Fnf","fallback_lid":"tg_limited","type":"tag","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"}},{"val":1,"tag":{"id":"7bgKfX3rQm4ObZzN7i7ev","fallback_lid":"tg_turn","type":"tag","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"}}],"sp":0,"uses":0,"actions":[],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[],"description":"Gained from the <i>Walking Armory: Rank II</i> pilot talent.","type":"System"},"folder":null,"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"9RbPb3wUJLjXltEQ","name":"EXTERNAL BATTERIES","permission":{"default":0,"kDiJJdMOROJNqvmU":3},"type":"mech_system","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[],"deployables":[],"destroyed":false,"effect":"Weapons that deal any energy gain +5 RANGE if they are ranged or +1 THREAT if they are melee. When you take any structure damage, this system is destroyed and you take 1d6 AP explosive damage from the explosion. This damage can’t be prevented or reduced in any way.","lid":"ms_external_batteries","integrated":[],"license":"TOKUGAWA","license_level":1,"name":"EXTERNAL BATTERIES","source":{"id":"3wB3mYKitmiMMsMexoSWW","fallback_lid":"HA","type":"manufacturer","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"},"tags":[{"tag":{"id":"3s9x9kN8UpSVrXnvEk9Uq","fallback_lid":"tg_unique","type":"tag","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"}}],"sp":2,"uses":0,"actions":[],"bonuses":[{"lid":"range","val":"1","damage_types":{"Burn":false,"Energy":true,"Explosive":false,"Heat":false,"Kinetic":false,"Variable":false},"range_types":{"Blast":false,"Burst":false,"Cone":false,"Line":false,"Range":false,"Thrown":false,"Threat":true},"weapon_types":{"CQB":false,"Cannon":false,"Launcher":false,"Melee":true,"Nexus":false,"Rifle":false},"weapon_sizes":{"Auxiliary":true,"Heavy":true,"Main":true,"Superheavy":true},"overwrite":false,"replace":false},{"lid":"range","val":"5","damage_types":{"Burn":false,"Energy":true,"Explosive":false,"Heat":false,"Kinetic":false,"Variable":false},"range_types":{"Blast":false,"Burst":false,"Cone":false,"Line":false,"Range":true,"Thrown":false,"Threat":false},"weapon_types":{"CQB":true,"Cannon":true,"Launcher":true,"Melee":false,"Nexus":true,"Rifle":true},"weapon_sizes":{"Auxiliary":true,"Heavy":true,"Main":true,"Superheavy":true},"overwrite":false,"replace":false}],"synergies":[],"description":"External batteries are by no means unique; however, according to Harrison Armory marketing, POWERALL cells are the longest-lasting, fastest cycling, and highest capacity solid-state cells available. A side-effect of their high capacity is a proportionate increase in volatility, but pilots must agree to absolve Harrison Armory of any liability prior to receiving print authorization.","type":"System"},"folder":null,"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"AOil221N38KVKpD2","name":"WHITEWASH SEALANT SPRAY","permission":{"default":0,"kDiJJdMOROJNqvmU":3},"type":"mech_system","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[],"deployables":[],"destroyed":false,"effect":"","lid":"ms_whitewash_sealant_spray","integrated":[],"license":"LANCASTER","license_level":2,"name":"WHITEWASH SEALANT SPRAY","source":{"id":"HnhUqNAPy7nMHu7TP05sG","fallback_lid":"IPS-N","type":"manufacturer","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"},"tags":[],"sp":2,"uses":0,"actions":[{"lid":"act_88r03jsUkKxEW3FXonYWD","name":"New Action","activation":"Quick","terse":"Terse Description","detail":"This sealant can be sprayed on characters or free spaces within range 5 and line of sight. It has different effects depending on the target:<ul><li><b>Hostile Characters:</b> Your target must succeed on an Agility save or they become Slowed until the end of their next turn and clear all burn.</li><li><b>Allied Characters:</b> Your target clears all burn but they become Slowed until the end of their next turn.</li><li><b>Free Space:</b> Any fires within blast 1 are extinguished and the area becomes difficult terrain for the rest of the scene.</li></ul>","cost":1,"frequency":"","init":"","trigger":"","pilot":false,"mech":true,"heat_cost":0,"synergy_locations":[],"damage":[],"range":[],"confirm":["CONFIRM undefined"],"hide_active":false,"ignore_used":false,"log":""}],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[],"description":"For fire suppression and fast, temporary seals in punctured starship bulkheads, IPS-N offers a range of single-use, single objective nanites – “whitewash”. This sealant spray can also be used to restrain noncompliant actors when the correct spray heads and catalytic formulations are installed to the applicator.","type":"System"},"folder":null,"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"BhGQGBMJOfpG9MZw","name":"FERROUS LASH","permission":{"default":0,"kDiJJdMOROJNqvmU":3},"type":"mech_system","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[],"deployables":[],"destroyed":false,"effect":"","lid":"ms_ferrous_lash","integrated":[],"license":"BLACK WITCH","license_level":1,"name":"FERROUS LASH","source":{"id":"uxjxh4Hl1iIg58Wcx3S_m","fallback_lid":"SSC","type":"manufacturer","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"},"tags":[],"sp":2,"uses":0,"actions":[{"lid":"act_FfZd1TiypyWkaBUkfwApN","name":"New Action","activation":"Quick","terse":"Terse Description","detail":"Choose a character within range 8 and line of sight. If they are allied, you may pull them 5 spaces in any direction; if they are hostile, they must succeed on an Agility save or be pulled 5 spaces in a direction of your choice. This movement ignores engagement and doesn’t provoke reactions.<br>If a hostile target moved by this system collides with an obstruction or another mech, they stop moving and are knocked Prone.","cost":1,"frequency":"","init":"","trigger":"","pilot":false,"mech":true,"heat_cost":0,"synergy_locations":[],"damage":[],"range":[],"confirm":["CONFIRM undefined"],"hide_active":false,"ignore_used":false,"log":""}],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[],"description":"Initially developed as a nonlethal crowd-suppression device, the Ferrous Lash is a far more complex and dangerous device in the hands of the right pilot. The Lash consists of a series of integrated launchers that detonate payloads of fast-congealing ferrofluids that restrain their targets. Tuned to the correct frequency, these proprietary ferrofluid blends form into rudimentary ambulatory segments, pulling their hosts back towards the one wielding the Lash.","type":"System"},"folder":null,"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
{"_id":"CFU6EjM6wEYZEUdD","name":"ACESO STABILIZER","permission":{"default":0,"kDiJJdMOROJNqvmU":3},"type":"mech_system","data":{"cascading":false,"counters":[],"deployables":[],"destroyed":false,"effect":"","lid":"ms_aceso_stabilizer","integrated":[],"license":"LANCASTER","license_level":3,"name":"ACESO STABILIZER","source":{"id":"HnhUqNAPy7nMHu7TP05sG","fallback_lid":"IPS-N","type":"manufacturer","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"},"tags":[{"val":3,"tag":{"id":"6i_N-6rNndy5Q8xPU9Fnf","fallback_lid":"tg_limited","type":"tag","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"}},{"tag":{"id":"rCLjPUZxgUqYq6gGlfCrE","fallback_lid":"tg_overshield","type":"tag","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"}},{"tag":{"id":"m4L8W_LqSLTGOqxV78i-U","fallback_lid":"tg_shield","type":"tag","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"}},{"tag":{"id":"3s9x9kN8UpSVrXnvEk9Uq","fallback_lid":"tg_unique","type":"tag","reg_name":"compendium|compendium"}}],"sp":3,"uses":0,"actions":[{"lid":"act_mhrBksFE3HeZpkBv125Az","name":"New Action","activation":"Quick","terse":"Terse Description","detail":"Expend a charge to fire this small, self-arming system onto an allied mech within range 5. They gain Overshield equal to your Grit +4. While they have this Overshield they gain Immunity to Impaired and Jammed.","cost":1,"frequency":"","init":"","trigger":"","pilot":false,"mech":true,"heat_cost":0,"synergy_locations":[],"damage":[],"range":[],"confirm":["CONFIRM undefined"],"hide_active":false,"ignore_used":false,"log":""}],"bonuses":[],"synergies":[],"description":"The IPS-N Aceso Stabilizer is a useful triage measure for any scoring and minor mechanical damage that is sustained in the course of combat engagement or negative environmental interaction. Thanks to its negligible processor demand, Aceso Stabilizers can even be controlled by comp/con units – this allows the pilot to concentrate on complex repairs or immediate threat neutralization.","type":"System"},"folder":null,"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[]}
